fu.gps

Class GPSMeasurement

  • java.lang.Object
    • fu.gps.GPSPosition
      • fu.gps.GPSMeasurement
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class GPSMeasurement
extends GPSPosition
    A GPSPosition that stores the nearers measurements conditions: number of satellites, HDOP, DGSP condition and GPS timestamp.

    • Constructor Detail

      • GPSMeasurement

        public GPSMeasurement(GPSPosition pos)
        Creates a measurement from a given GPSPosition. All values appart from the actual positions are invalid.

      • GPSMeasurement

        public GPSMeasurement(java.lang.String text)
               throws GPSDecoderException
        Creates a measurement from a given string. A string may be formatted according to GPSPosition (31 chars) or may have the format >GPSPosition<,>#sats<,>HDOP<,>DGPS<,>TimeStamp< .
        Throws:
        GPSDecoderException

      • toExtendedString

        public java.lang.String toExtendedString()
        Create a printed version of the object, that can be used to create a new object using the textual constructor. Note that toString (of super) still only creates a representation of the position. This is, because string representaions (e.g. of LineArea) should be compatible.

      • getDGPS

        public int getDGPS()
        Returns the if Differential GPS was available for this measurement. The return value is one of {DGPS_FALSE, DGPS_TRUE}. Returns DGPS_UNSET (-1) if no value is available, but better use the isset method to check, if the value is available.
